# MCP Chrome Extension for t3.chat

This is a Chrome extension built with Plasmo that adds Model Context Protocol (MCP) capabilities to t3.chat.

## Project Context
- **Purpose**: Integrate MCP functionality into t3.chat webapp
- **Framework**: Plasmo for Chrome extension development
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v3
- **Target**: t3.chat website enhancement

## Development Guidelines
- Use context7 MCP for Plasmo documentation and best practices
- Follow Plasmo conventions for content scripts and UI components
- Implement MCP protocol integration for t3.chat
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Focus on seamless integration with t3.chat UI/UX
- Organize components in separate files for maintainability

## Component Structure
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Use TypeScript interfaces for type safety
- Store types in `src/types/` directory
- Store utilities in `src/utils/` directory
- Store components in `src/components/` directory
- Use kebab-case for all file names (e.g., `mcp-server-form.tsx`)
- Prefer named exports over default exports for consistency
- Convert user-input names to kebab-case using lodash

## Styling Standards
- Consistent Tailwind classes for forms, buttons, and layouts
- Use Radix UI for complex component behaviors
- Maintain clean, accessible UI patterns